Linus and Luke react to a class-action settlement where ParkMobile paid out $1 credits to customers after a data leak, while lawyers walked away with over $6 million. They break down how companies use settlements to avoid blame, why lawyers always win, and how little these payouts actually help real people.

Watch the full WAN Show: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YVHXYqMPyzc

Microsoft is removing known workarounds for creating local accounts in Windows 11, forcing users to sign in with a Microsoft account and internet connection. Linus and Luke talk about how this decision sums up Windows’ growing frustration, and why so many users are ready to jump ship to Linux or macOS.
